      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SENTIMENTAL LEGEND (3) bolted in two back before jumping in the market in the Roberts last time out. He couldn't sprint with them there, but gets a weight swing in his favour and the map favours here. Can sit closer this time around and turn the tables. ABERDEEN FLYER (1) was no match in the Lex Piper but he finished off strongly, showing his talents in the Roberts when storming home over the top. He rises in weight today, but he's won the main lead-up and there's no reason why he can't go on with the job. WYNN LAS VEGAS (4) went to the front and was simply too good as an odds-on pop at Pinjarra. The way he finished off there was very impressive and while he does jump to 2200m, it doesn't look an issue. Can take up the running and prove tough to run down. DOMINATUS (2) has disappointed his past couple but the fresh run suggested he was back in good order. Not willing to discount just yet. CARENTAN (7) is next best.",
